Hello Michael,

Thank you for taking the time to meet today.

Today we:
We looked into the AD_AccessChanges job and saw that it was apparently not progressing. After manually testing the script we found that there may be a bottleneck on the SQL server as it is checking against the new nasuni information for group access.
We changed the schedule on the AD jobs to run daily with the exception of the AD_AccessChange group which will run weekly on Fridays.
Looked into the scans and made sure they were working to the nasuni.
We setup the proxy server to scan your cloud based nasuni device as well.

Our next steps are:
You will:
Monitor the scans to ensure they are working as expected once they have finished.
I will:
Follow up after the Friday scan to validate the scan completed.





Thank you,

Hey Michael,

Apologies for the delayed meeting summary, but I appreciate you meeting with me this week. To recap our meeting, we:


	Removed the host mapping feature from the FSAC System Scan- this appears to resolve the issue of NEA querying every host against every agent



	
	
		Once we did this, we had a successful scan- minus the one host who does not have an agent configured for monitoring yet
		We also see the activity data correlating to the correct hosts in the AIC
	
	



	Removed the analysis tasks from various weekly reports as the table is already being created when the job runs, these jobs are just used to create a filtered report from the already collected data. This should increase their speed.
	Removed the Group Usage group from File System Activity and moved it to the AD Activity group where it belongs
	Found AIC Effective Access Report was still not displaying for deeper than the first couple of folder levels, but this looks to be caused by the fact we don’t have rights to read permissions on the deeper levels.
	Removed a second DC from the ADI scan that was within the same domain already being scanned.



Once you've had a chance to work out those Access Denied errors on your Nasuni filers and give the connection profile account at least rights to view permissions (Local Admin is recommended) let me know how things in the AIC look!

Thank you,

Tay Caliguiri

Senior Technical Support Engineer

Looked into the activity not populating in the nasuni heavy server.

Good morning!

My azr-nasuni scan is still chugging along so I don’t have any update with that.
When JobsGroup_FileSystem runs, it would also run all of the subfolders correct?  So running Group_FileSystem would also run…

  *   GroupFileSystemGroup_0.CollectionGroup_3.Activity
  *   GroupFileSystemGroup_0.Collection-AzureNasuni

I am wondering if I want to run the two jobs independently so that the on prem is not held up by the azure-nasuni collection. Does that make sense?

If I do that then I won’t run any of the other FileSystem subjobs like open access, direct permissions or broken inheritance….



[cid:image004.png@01DB9261.D9A95D80]


My concern is I need activity information daily.  I do not need permission activity daily.

If you only need portions daily I would schedule those separately and disable the full file system scheduled task as it is basically causing those jobs to be run twice.

Hey Michael,

Apologies for the delayed meeting summary, but I appreciate you meeting with me this week. To recap our meeting, we:


	Removed the host mapping feature from the FSAC System Scan- this appears to resolve the issue of NEA querying every host against every agent



	 



	
	
		Once we did this, we had a successful scan- minus the one host who does not have an agent configured for monitoring yet
		We also see the activity data correlating to the correct hosts in the AIC
	
	



	Removed the analysis tasks from various weekly reports as the table is already being created when the job runs, these jobs are just used to create a filtered report from the already collected data. This should increase their speed.
	Removed the Group Usage group from File System Activity and moved it to the AD Activity group where it belongs
	Found AIC Effective Access Report was still not displaying for deeper than the first couple of folder levels, but this looks to be caused by the fact we don’t have rights to read permissions on the deeper levels.
	Removed a second DC from the ADI scan that was within the same domain already being scanned.



Once you've had a chance to work out those Access Denied errors on your Nasuni filers and give the connection profile account at least rights to view permissions (Local Admin is recommended) let me know how things in the AIC look!

Thank you,

	Removed the host mapping feature from the FSAC System Scan- this appears to resolve the issue of NEA querying every host against every agent



	 



	 



	
	
		Once we did this, we had a successful scan- minus the one host who does not have an agent configured for monitoring yet
		We also see the activity data correlating to the correct hosts in the AIC
	
	



	Removed the analysis tasks from various weekly reports as the table is already being created when the job runs, these jobs are just used to create a filtered report from the already collected data. This should increase their speed.
	Removed the Group Usage group from File System Activity and moved it to the AD Activity group where it belongs
	Found AIC Effective Access Report was still not displaying for deeper than the first couple of folder levels, but this looks to be caused by the fact we don’t have rights to read permissions on the deeper levels.
	Removed a second DC from the ADI scan that was within the same domain already being scanned.

TextBody:
Hello Michael,

The job you are looking for is the the 0.Collections and 0.Collections-AzureNasuni groups.

Inside these groups you will see an FSAC scan and and FSAC bulk import job. Right now the bulk import needs to be run on both.
When you schedule the jobs make sure FSAC scan, then FSAC bulk import run in that order. The scan will collect the information, the bulk import moves it into the SQL database. The error you are seeing is because right now the scan has run but bulk import has not so it needs to import the data so it doesn't overwrite what it already has collected.

Thank you,

Hello Michael,

The job you are looking for is the the 0.Collections and 0.Collections-AzureNasuni groups.

Inside these groups you will see an FSAC scan and and FSAC bulk import job. Right now the bulk import needs to be run on both.
When you schedule the jobs make sure FSAC scan, then FSAC bulk import run in that order. The scan will collect the information, the bulk import moves it into the SQL database. The error you are seeing is because right now the scan has run but bulk import has not so it needs to import the data so it doesn't overwrite what it already has collected.

Thank you,

Hello Michael,

The job you are looking for is the the 0.Collections and 0.Collections-AzureNasuni groups.

Inside these groups you will see an FSAC scan and and FSAC bulk import job. Right now the bulk import needs to be run on both.
When you schedule the jobs make sure FSAC scan, then FSAC bulk import run in that order. The scan will collect the information, the bulk import moves it into the SQL database. The error you are seeing is because right now the scan has run but bulk import has not so it needs to import the data so it doesn't overwrite what it already has collected.

Thank you,

Hello Michael,

The job you are looking for is the the 0.Collections and 0.Collections-AzureNasuni groups.

Inside these groups you will see an FSAC scan and and FSAC bulk import job. Right now the bulk import needs to be run on both.
When you schedule the jobs make sure FSAC scan, then FSAC bulk import run in that order. The scan will collect the information, the bulk import moves it into the SQL database. The error you are seeing is because right now the scan has run but bulk import has not so it needs to import the data so it doesn't overwrite what it already has collected.

Thank you,

Hello Michael,

The job you are looking for is the the 0.Collections and 0.Collections-AzureNasuni groups.

Inside these groups you will see an FSAC scan and and FSAC bulk import job. Right now the bulk import needs to be run on both.
When you schedule the jobs make sure FSAC scan, then FSAC bulk import run in that order. The scan will collect the information, the bulk import moves it into the SQL database. The error you are seeing is because right now the scan has run but bulk import has not so it needs to import the data so it doesn't overwrite what it already has collected.

Hello Michael,

The job you are looking for is the the 0.Collections and 0.Collections-AzureNasuni groups.

Inside these groups you will see an FSAC scan and and FSAC bulk import job. Right now the bulk import needs to be run on both.
When you schedule the jobs make sure FSAC scan, then FSAC bulk import run in that order. The scan will collect the information, the bulk import moves it into the SQL database. The error you are seeing is because right now the scan has run but bulk import has not so it needs to import the data so it doesn't overwrite what it already has collected.

Thank you,

TextBody:
Hello Michael,

Thank you for your time and patience on this issue and I am glad that we were able to get your issue resolved for you. 


If you require assistance in the future, please feel free to open a ticket and we'd be happy to assist with any additional problems you may have.
Normally our tickets are assigned to the next available engineer, but once you get a ticket assigned, we can try to accommodate if you would like to work with a specific engineer if they are available. If you are assigned a different engineer feel free to ask them to reassign it to your preferred engineer and if they are available we will do so.


The following is a summary of the ticket for your records.

Issue:
Activity Information only showing for one Nasuni device.


Resolution:
- Removed the host mapping feature from the FSAC System Scan- this appears to resolve the issue of NEA querying every host against every agent
--- Once we did this, we had a successful scan- minus the one host who does not have an agent configured for monitoring yet
--- We also see the activity data correlating to the correct hosts in the AIC

- Removed the analysis tasks from various weekly reports as the table is already being created when the job runs, these jobs are just used to create a filtered report from the already collected data. This should increase their speed.

-Removed the Group Usage group from File System Activity and moved it to the AD Activity group where it belongs

-Found AIC Effective Access Report was still not displaying for deeper than the first couple of folder levels, but this looks to be caused by the fact we don’t have rights to read permissions on the deeper levels.

-Removed a second DC from the ADI scan that was within the same domain already being scanned.

At this time I will be closing your ticket out for you. This case can be re-opened at any time if any related issues return. 
Please feel free to reach out to the Netwrix team if you have any additional questions or would like assistance with any issues. Following this email, you will receive an automated confirmation that the case has been closed.
You will also receive a survey link, it would help us greatly to improve our support service if you could provide any feedback that you may have regarding your experience with this case.

Thank you,
Ian Ranstrom

Hello Michael,

The job you are looking for is the the 0.Collections and 0.Collections-AzureNasuni groups.

Inside these groups you will see an FSAC scan and and FSAC bulk import job. Right now the bulk import needs to be run on both.
When you schedule the jobs make sure FSAC scan, then FSAC bulk import run in that order. The scan will collect the information, the bulk import moves it into the SQL database. The error you are seeing is because right now the scan has run but bulk import has not so it needs to import the data so it doesn't overwrite what it already has collected.

Thank you,
